Epigallocatechin gallate (EGCG) and astragalin were obtained from Amore Pacific (Yongin, South Korea). EGCG glucosides were prepared as described previously (Moon et al. 2006). Rutin and ampelospsin were purchased from Acros Organics (NJ, USA) and ZR Chemicals (Shanghai, China), respectively. Others chemicals were purchased from Sigma. For initial screening, each compound was either dissolved in dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO) or distilled water to obtain 10 mM of stock solution. The reaction mixture contained 26 μM FRET substrate, 8.7 μg enzyme, and 100 μM inhibitor in 50 mM Tris/HCl (pH 7.0). The reaction was run at 25 °C for 11 min. Inhibition activity was calculated using the following Eq. (1):1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
